# Developing with TypeScript

TypeScript 5.x development with type system, generics, utility types, and strict mode patterns.

## When to Use

- Writing React components
- Defining API types and interfaces
- Creating utility functions
- Working with complex type transformations

## Key Patterns

### Strict Types
```typescript
// Enable in tsconfig.json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "strict": true,
    "noImplicitAny": true,
    "strictNullChecks": true
  }
}
```

### Interface vs Type
```typescript
// Use interface for object shapes (extendable)
interface Task {
  id: number;
  title: string;
  status: TaskStatus;
}

// Use type for unions, intersections, mapped types
type TaskStatus = 'todo' | 'in_progress' | 'review' | 'done';
type TaskWithAssignee = Task & { assignee: User };
```

### Generics
```typescript
// Generic API response
interface ApiResponse<T> {
  data: T;
  meta: {
    total: number;
    page: number;
  };
}

async function fetchTasks(): Promise<ApiResponse<Task[]>> {
  const response = await fetch('/api/v1/tasks');
  return response.json();
}
```

### Utility Types
```typescript
// Partial for optional fields
type TaskUpdate = Partial<Task>;

// Pick for subset
type TaskSummary = Pick<Task, 'id' | 'title' | 'status'>;

// Omit to exclude fields
type TaskCreate = Omit<Task, 'id' | 'createdAt'>;

// Record for dictionaries
type TasksByStatus = Record<TaskStatus, Task[]>;
```

### Type Guards
```typescript
function isTask(value: unknown): value is Task {
  return (
    typeof value === 'object' &&
    value !== null &&
    'id' in value &&
    'title' in value
  );
}
```

## Best Practices

1. **Enable strict mode** - Catch errors at compile time
2. **Avoid `any`** - Use `unknown` if type is truly unknown
3. **Explicit return types** - For public APIs
4. **Const assertions** - For literal types: `as const`
5. **Discriminated unions** - For state machines

# Developing with React

React 18+ development with hooks, state management, component patterns, and Next.js integration.

## When to Use

- Building UI components
- Managing component state
- Integrating with APIs via React Query
- Creating forms and handling user input

## Key Patterns

### Functional Components
```typescript
interface TaskCardProps {
  task: Task;
  onStatusChange: (status: TaskStatus) => void;
}

export function TaskCard({ task, onStatusChange }: TaskCardProps) {
  return (
    <div className="rounded-lg border p-4">
      <h3 className="font-semibold">{task.title}</h3>
      <StatusBadge status={task.status} />
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Hooks
```typescript
// useState for local state
const [isEditing, setIsEditing] = useState(false);

// useEffect for side effects
useEffect(() => {
  document.title = `Task: ${task.title}`;
}, [task.title]);

// useCallback for memoized callbacks
const handleSubmit = useCallback((data: TaskCreate) => {
  createTask.mutate(data);
}, [createTask]);

// useMemo for expensive computations
const filteredTasks = useMemo(
  () => tasks.filter(t => t.status === filter),
  [tasks, filter]
);
```

### React Query for Server State
```typescript
// Fetching
const { data, isLoading, error } = useQuery({
  queryKey: ['tasks'],
  queryFn: fetchTasks,
});

// Mutations
const createTask = useMutation({
  mutationFn: (data: TaskCreate) => api.post('/tasks', data),
  onSuccess: () => {
    queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['tasks'] });
  },
});
```

### Zustand for Client State
```typescript
interface FilterStore {
  status: TaskStatus | null;
  setStatus: (status: TaskStatus | null) => void;
}

export const useFilterStore = create<FilterStore>((set) => ({
  status: null,
  setStatus: (status) => set({ status }),
}));
```

### Form Handling
```typescript
function TaskForm({ onSubmit }: { onSubmit: (data: TaskCreate) => void }) {
  const [title, setTitle] = useState('');
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);

  const handleSubmit = (e: React.FormEvent) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    if (!title.trim()) {
      setError('Title is required');
      return;
    }
    onSubmit({ title });
  };

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
      <input
        value={title}
        onChange={(e) => setTitle(e.target.value)}
        className="border rounded px-3 py-2"
      />
      {error && <p className="text-red-500 text-sm">{error}</p>}
    </form>
  );
}
```

## Best Practices

1. **Lift state minimally** - Keep state close to where it's used
2. **Use React Query** - For all server state
3. **Avoid prop drilling** - Use context or Zustand
4. **Memoize appropriately** - Don't over-optimize
5. **Test with RTL** - Focus on user behavior, not implementation

# Jest

Execute and generate Jest tests for JavaScript/TypeScript projects with React Testing Library.

## When to Use

- Writing unit tests for React components
- Testing TypeScript utilities
- Mocking modules and APIs
- Testing hooks and state

## Key Patterns

### Basic Test
```typescript
describe('formatDate', () => {
  it('formats date in locale format', () => {
    const date = new Date('2024-01-15');
    expect(formatDate(date)).toBe('January 15, 2024');
  });
});
```

### Component Testing
```typescript
import { render, screen, fireEvent } from '@testing-library/react';
import { TaskCard } from './TaskCard';

describe('TaskCard', () => {
  const mockTask = {
    id: 1,
    title: 'Test Task',
    status: 'todo' as const,
  };

  it('displays task title', () => {
    render(<TaskCard task={mockTask} onStatusChange={jest.fn()} />);
    expect(screen.getByText('Test Task')).toBeInTheDocument();
  });

  it('calls onStatusChange when status button clicked', () => {
    const onStatusChange = jest.fn();
    render(<TaskCard task={mockTask} onStatusChange={onStatusChange} />);

    fireEvent.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /start/i }));

    expect(onStatusChange).toHaveBeenCalledWith('in_progress');
  });
});
```

### Async Testing
```typescript
import { waitFor } from '@testing-library/react';

it('loads and displays tasks', async () => {
  render(<TaskList />);

  await waitFor(() => {
    expect(screen.getByText('Task 1')).toBeInTheDocument();
  });
});
```

### Mocking
```typescript
// Mock module
jest.mock('../api/tasks', () => ({
  fetchTasks: jest.fn().mockResolvedValue([
    { id: 1, title: 'Task 1' },
  ]),
}));

// Mock fetch
global.fetch = jest.fn().mockResolvedValue({
  ok: true,
  json: () => Promise.resolve({ data: [] }),
});
```

### Testing Hooks
```typescript
import { renderHook, act } from '@testing-library/react';
import { useCounter } from './useCounter';

describe('useCounter', () => {
  it('increments counter', () => {
    const { result } = renderHook(() => useCounter());

    act(() => {
      result.current.increment();
    });

    expect(result.current.count).toBe(1);
  });
});
```

### React Query Testing
```typescript
import { QueryClient, QueryClientProvider } from '@tanstack/react-query';

const createWrapper = () => {
  const queryClient = new QueryClient({
    defaultOptions: { queries: { retry: false } },
  });
  return ({ children }) => (
    <QueryClientProvider client={queryClient}>
      {children}
    </QueryClientProvider>
  );
};

it('fetches tasks', async () => {
  const { result } = renderHook(() => useTasks(), {
    wrapper: createWrapper(),
  });

  await waitFor(() => expect(result.current.isSuccess).toBe(true));
});
```

## Commands

```bash
# Run all tests
npm test

# Run with coverage
npm test -- --coverage

# Run specific file
npm test -- TaskCard.test.tsx

# Run in watch mode
npm test -- --watch

# Update snapshots
npm test -- -u
```

## Best Practices

1. **Test behavior, not implementation** - Focus on what user sees
2. **Use screen queries** - Prefer `getByRole`, `getByText`
3. **Avoid testing internals** - Don't test state directly
4. **One assertion per test** - When possible
5. **Clear test names** - Describe expected behavior

# Writing Playwright Tests

Patterns for writing maintainable E2E test scripts with Playwright, focusing on selector strategies, page objects, and wait handling.

## When to Use

- Writing end-to-end tests
- Testing critical user flows
- Cross-browser testing
- Visual regression testing

## Key Patterns

### Basic Test
```typescript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test('user can create a task', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/');

  await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'New Task' }).click();
  await page.getByLabel('Title').fill('My New Task');
  await page.getByLabel('Priority').selectOption('high');
  await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Create' }).click();

  await expect(page.getByText('My New Task')).toBeVisible();
});
```

### Page Object Model
```typescript
// pages/TasksPage.ts
export class TasksPage {
  constructor(private page: Page) {}

  async goto() {
    await this.page.goto('/tasks');
  }

  async createTask(title: string, priority: string) {
    await this.page.getByRole('button', { name: 'New Task' }).click();
    await this.page.getByLabel('Title').fill(title);
    await this.page.getByLabel('Priority').selectOption(priority);
    await this.page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Create' }).click();
  }

  async getTaskCard(title: string) {
    return this.page.getByRole('article').filter({ hasText: title });
  }
}

// tests/tasks.spec.ts
test('create task flow', async ({ page }) => {
  const tasksPage = new TasksPage(page);
  await tasksPage.goto();
  await tasksPage.createTask('New Task', 'high');

  const taskCard = await tasksPage.getTaskCard('New Task');
  await expect(taskCard).toBeVisible();
});
```

### Selectors
```typescript
// Prefer role selectors (accessible)
page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Submit' });
page.getByRole('textbox', { name: 'Email' });
page.getByRole('heading', { level: 1 });

// Text selectors for visible text
page.getByText('Welcome');
page.getByLabel('Password');
page.getByPlaceholder('Search...');

// Test IDs as last resort
page.getByTestId('task-card-123');
```

### Waiting and Assertions
```typescript
// Auto-waiting (built-in)
await page.getByRole('button').click(); // Waits for actionable

// Explicit waiting
await page.waitForURL('**/dashboard');
await page.waitForResponse('**/api/tasks');

// Assertions with auto-retry
await expect(page.getByText('Success')).toBeVisible();
await expect(page.getByRole('list')).toHaveCount(5);
```

### API Mocking
```typescript
test('displays error on API failure', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.route('**/api/tasks', route => {
    route.fulfill({ status: 500, body: 'Server Error' });
  });

  await page.goto('/tasks');
  await expect(page.getByText('Failed to load tasks')).toBeVisible();
});
```

### Authentication
```typescript
// fixtures/auth.ts
test.use({
  storageState: 'playwright/.auth/user.json',
});

// Setup auth once
const authFile = 'playwright/.auth/user.json';

setup('authenticate', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/login');
  await page.getByLabel('Email').fill('user@example.com');
  await page.getByLabel('Password').fill('password');
  await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Sign in' }).click();
  await page.waitForURL('/dashboard');
  await page.context().storageState({ path: authFile });
});
```

## Commands

```bash
# Run all tests
npx playwright test

# Run with UI
npx playwright test --ui

# Run specific file
npx playwright test tasks.spec.ts

# Debug mode
npx playwright test --debug

# Generate tests
npx playwright codegen localhost:3000
```

## Best Practices

1. **Use page objects** - Reduce duplication
2. **Prefer role selectors** - Better accessibility
3. **Avoid hard waits** - Use auto-waiting
4. **Isolate tests** - Each test starts fresh
5. **Use fixtures** - For common setup

# Styling with Tailwind

Utility-first CSS styling patterns using Tailwind CSS 3.x for responsive designs, dark mode, and component styling.

## When to Use

- Styling React components
- Creating responsive layouts
- Implementing dark mode
- Building consistent UI

## Key Patterns

### Basic Styling
```tsx
// Spacing, colors, typography
<div className="p-4 bg-white rounded-lg shadow">
  <h2 className="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Task Title</h2>
  <p className="mt-2 text-gray-600">Description here</p>
</div>
```

### Responsive Design
```tsx
// Mobile-first approach
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
  {tasks.map(task => (
    <TaskCard key={task.id} task={task} />
  ))}
</div>

// Responsive text
<h1 className="text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold">
  Dashboard
</h1>
```

### Flexbox & Grid
```tsx
// Flexbox for alignment
<div className="flex items-center justify-between">
  <span>{task.title}</span>
  <StatusBadge status={task.status} />
</div>

// Grid for layouts
<div className="grid grid-cols-4 gap-4">
  <div className="col-span-3">Main content</div>
  <div className="col-span-1">Sidebar</div>
</div>
```

### States & Interactions
```tsx
// Hover, focus, active states
<button className="
  px-4 py-2 rounded-lg
  bg-blue-600 text-white
  hover:bg-blue-700
